<?xml version="1.1" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<databaseChangeLog
    xmlns="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog
        http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog/dbchangelog-3.6.xsd">

    <!--
        Phase E.6 Tier 3 — Ophthalmology Visit CRF template.

        Seeds a reusable "OPHTH_VISIT" CRF (v1.0) with the four sections
        every MUW ophthalmology study collects at every clinical visit:

          1. Visual Acuity (LogMAR + ETDRS, per-eye)
          2. Intraocular Pressure (per-eye, mmHg) + method
          3. Refraction (manifest: sphere / cylinder / axis, per-eye)
          4. Lens status (Phakic / Pseudophakic / Aphakic, per-eye)

        This is NOT context=demo — it runs on every MUW deployment so
        the CRF is immediately usable as a template for new studies.
        Tier 2's "reusable response sets" surface automatically via the
        M-B virtual-catalog backend once this CRF references them.

        IDs allocated assuming the demo seed
        (lc-muw-2026-06-01-seed-demo-data.xml) is the only prior
        contributor of CRF metadata:

          - crf_id = 2                (demo used 1)
          - crf_version_id = 2        (demo used 1)
          - section_id = 3..6         (demo used 1..2)
          - response_set_id = 3..7    (demo used 1..2)
          - item_id = 6..20           (demo used 1..5)
          - item_form_metadata_id = 6..20 (demo used 1..5)

        Item naming convention: `<DOMAIN>_<EYE>_<SUBFIELD>` so SAS
        operators can pattern-match per-eye columns in exports.

        Per-eye items (OD = right, OS = left) use LEFT_ITEM_TEXT for
        the eye label so the rendered form puts "Right eye (OD): [ ]"
        and "Left eye (OS): [ ]" side-by-side under each section
        header. The longer-form prompts ("LogMAR (decimal)") live in
        the section title; item-level RIGHT_ITEM_TEXT carries the unit
        suffix where applicable.

        Response sets seeded (Tier 2 deliverable, embedded here per
        plan: response sets become "catalog" entries once a CRF
        references them):

          - rs_id=3  LogMAR     (single-select, 25 options -0.3..+2.0 step 0.1)
          - rs_id=4  Snellen    (single-select, 20/16..20/400 + CF/HM/LP/NLP/NR)
          - rs_id=5  IOP units  (single-select, "mmHg" only — documents unit)
          - rs_id=6  Lens status (radio, Phakic / Pseudophakic / Aphakic)
          - rs_id=7  freetext   (text, required by item_form_metadata
                                 even on REAL / INT items)

        ETDRS letters (0-100) use response_set_id=7 (freetext) +
        item_data_type=INT + regexp range check, NOT a discrete
        select — there are too many values (101) for a usable
        dropdown.
    -->

    <changeSet author="muw-ophthalmology" id="2026-06-05-ophth-visit-crf-metadata">
        <comment>OPHTH_VISIT CRF v1.0 — 1 crf + 1 crf_version + 4 sections + 15 items + 5 response_sets + 15 item_form_metadata.</comment>

        <!-- ============================================================
             CRF + version
             ============================================================ -->
        <insert tableName="crf">
            <column name="crf_id" valueNumeric="2"/>
